piracy theory, anti-Semitism, and whiteness, all inscribed one way or another by pigeon matters, and seen through the anguished eyes of a birdphobe. This bestiary experiment through a phobic gaze concludes with a critique on the visual trope in anthropology's self-reflexive turn.An ethnographer with a taste for philosophy, Song writes in a distinctive descriptive and analytical style, obsessed with his locale and its inhabitants, constantly monitoring his own reactions and his impact on others, but always teasing out larger implications to his subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAnimal rights activistszPennsylvania. 0aPigeon shootingxMoral and ethical aspectszPennsylvania. 0aPigeon shootingxPolitical aspectszPennsylvania. 4aFolklore. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aAnthropology.  aFolklore.  aLinguistics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Social Sciencesz978311041361808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220009640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812200096423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812200096/original  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041361-8  Penn Press eBook Package Social Sciences  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  